transcription.text:
Speaker 1: Hi, this is Viagra.

Speaker 2: Hello.

Speaker 1: Hello, how are we doing sir?

Speaker 2: Hi, good morning, good afternoon, sorry.

Speaker 1: I'm calling to cancel my subscription.

Speaker 2: Are you here? Are you there?

Speaker 1: Yes.

Speaker 2: Okay, because I hear voices behind you.

Speaker 1: I'm calling to cancel my subscription.

Speaker 2: Actually, I never knew I subscribed until I started getting billed.

Speaker 1: It's been a while now.

Speaker 2: I sent an email, nothing was done.

Speaker 1: I just want to call and cancel.

Speaker 2: Yes, that's fine.

Speaker 1: Mr. Nosa?

Speaker 2: Yes.

Speaker 1: Yes, so you're not on the actual subscription,

Speaker 2: but just Dr. Jones wrote your prescription with refills.

Speaker 1: If you don't need refills, you don't need to lose the prescription.

Speaker 2: What you can do, and I can do that for you,

Speaker 1: is to pause the prescription so you're not on a monthly basis anymore,

Speaker 2: and you can call to reorder as needed,

Speaker 1: which allows you to save the price that you have

Speaker 2: and not have a more expensive price in the future, basically.

Speaker 1: You're just not going to get billed every month anymore.

Speaker 2: You're monthly going to be stopped, basically.

Speaker 1: Yes, I think I want to cancel everything,

Speaker 2: the subscription, the monthly billing, just everything.

Speaker 1: Okay.

Speaker 2: Yes, I'm canceling the prescription here for you.

Speaker 1: Only thing, if anything changes in the future,

Speaker 2: because they're going to have to refinance a new doctor prescription for you,

Speaker 1: your price will be up, okay?

Speaker 2: But I'll cancel everything for you.

Speaker 1: You're all set.

Speaker 2: Okay, but the one that's up, because it just charged me $200 and something.

Speaker 1: Can I get a refund?

Speaker 2: Yes, if you want one, you get it, because it has shipped.

Speaker 1: You're going to see a tracking number in your mail.

Speaker 2: Just write refuse return to the sender on it for a refund, okay?

Speaker 1: Once I receive it, send it back?

Speaker 2: Yes, just write refuse return on the packet when you receive it.

Speaker 1: Leave it in your mailbox.

Speaker 2: The mailman is going to take that back to us.

Speaker 1: Okay, thank you.

Speaker 2: You're welcome.

Speaker 1: All right, bye.

Speaker 2: Bye-bye.
